hern_Nations,_Nationalities,_and_Peoples%27_Region.svg|20px]] [[Southern Nations, Nationalities, and People's Region|SNNPR]]\n| '''65.4%'''\n| '''77.8%'''\n| ''27.6%''\n| ''19.9%''\n| ''34.8%''\n| ''55.5%''\n| ''3.0%''\n| ''2.4%''\n| 16.7%\n| 14.1%\n| 15.4%\n| 6.6%\n|\n| 1.5%\n|-\n| [[File:Flag_of_the_Tigray_Region.svg|20px]] [[Tigray Region|Tigray]]\n| '''95.9%'''\n| '''96.1%'''\n| ''95.5%''\n| ''95.6%''\n|\n| ''0.1%''\n| ''0.4%''\n| ''0.4%''\n| 4.1%\n| 4.0%\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Bah\u00e1\u02bc\u00ed Faith in Ethiopia]]\n* [[Buda (folklore)]]\n* [[Catholic Church in Ethiopia]]\n* [[Christianity in Ethiopia]]\n* [[Demographics of Ethiopia]]\n* [[Ethiopian Catholic Church]]\n* [[Beta Israel|Ethiopian Jews]]\n* [[Ethiopian Orthodox Tewahedo Church]]\n* [[Islam in Ethiopia]]\n* [[P'ent'ay (Ethiopian Evangelicalism)]]\n* [[Z\u0101r]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n* {{CIA World Factbook|year=2006}}\n\n==External links==\n* Berhanu Abegaz, [http://bxabeg.people.wm.edu/Ethiopia.Census%20Portrait.pdf \"Ethiopia: A Model Nation of Minorities\"]\n\n{{Ethiopia topics}}\n{{Africa in topic|Religion in}}\n\n[[Category:Religion in Ethiopia| ]]\n", "name_user": "Magherbin", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOrthodox Christian-Muslim Relations", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Religion_in_Ethiopia"}
{"title_page": "I Love the Way You Love Me", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = I Love the Way You Love Me\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[John Michael Montgomery]]\n| album      = [[Life's a Dance]]\n| released   = March 1, 1993\n| format     = [[CD single]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Country music|Country]]\n| length     = 4:01\n| label      = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| writer     = [[Victoria Shaw (singer)|Victoria Shaw]], [[Chuck Cannon]]\n| producer   = [[Doug Johnson (record producer)|Doug Johnson]]\n| prev_title = [[Life's a Dance (song)|Life's a Dance]]\n| prev_year  = 1992\n| next_title = [[Beer and Bones]]\n| next_year  = 1993\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|OEhzwvVo6x8|\"I Love the Way You Love Me\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''I Love the Way You Love Me'''\" is a song recorded by American [[country music]] singer [[John Michael Montgomery]] from his debut album, ''[[Life's a Dance]]'' (1992). It was written by [[Victoria Shaw (singer)|Victoria Shaw]] and [[Chuck Cannon]], and released in March 1993 as the album's second single. The song reached the top of the US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot Country Singles & Tracks]] chart. It became Montgomery's first number-one single and was named Song of the Year by the [[Academy of Country Music]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.acmcountry.com/winners?term=John+Michael+Montgomery&name=wsearch&wsort=name&wdir=ASC |title=Winners - John Michael Montgomery |publisher=[[Academy of Country Music]] |accessdate=January 7, 2019 }}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video was directed by Marc Ball and premiered in early 1993.\n\n==Chart positions==\n\"I Love the Way You Love Me\" debuted at number 63 on the U.S. ''Billboard'' Hot Country Singles & Tracks for the week of March 13, 1993.\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (1993)\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canadacountry|1|chartid=0963|publishdate=May 29, 1993|accessdate=August 5, 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardhot100|60|artist=John Michael Montgomery}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcountrysongs|1|artist=John Michael Montgomery}}\n|}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (1993)\n!scope=\"col\"|Position\n|-\n| Canada Country Tracks (''[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?brws_s=1&file_num=nlc008388.2327&type=1&interval=24|title=RPM Top 100 Country Tracks of 1993|work=[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]|date=December 18, 1993|accessdate=August 5, 2013}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" | 7\n|-\n| US [[Hot Country Songs|Country Songs]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/1993/hot-country-songs| title=Best of 1993: Country Songs | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] | date=1993| accessdate=August 5, 2013}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" | 9\n|}\n\n==Boyzone version==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = I Love the Way You Love Me\n| cover      = Boyzone I Love The Way You Love Me.jpeg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Boyzone]]\n| album      = [[Where We Belong (album)|Where We Belong]]\n| released   = 23 November 1998\n| format     =\n| recorded   = 1998\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length     =\n| label      = [[Polydor]]\n| writer     = Victoria Shaw, Chuck Cannon\n| producer   = [[Steve Mac]], Rose & Foster\n| prev_title = [[No Matter What (Boyzone song)|No Matter What]]\n| prev_year  = 1998\n| next_title = [[When the Going Gets Tough, the Tough Get Going (song)#Boyzone version|When the Going Gets Tough]]\n| next_year  = 1999\n}}\n\n\"'''I Love the Way You Love Me'''\" was covered by the Irish [[boyband]] [[Boyzone]]. It was released on 23 November 1998 as the fifth single from their third album, ''[[Where We Belong (album)|Where We Belong]]''. The song has received a gold certification for shipping of 400,000 units in the UK.<ref>{{cite certification|region=United Kingdom|title=I Love the Way You Love Me}}</ref> The song became popular after its inclusion in an episode of [[EastEnders]].{{citation needed|date=September 2011}} \"I Love the Way You Love Me\" was re-produced by [[Steve Mac]] for its single release, with the album version being produced by Rose & Foster.\n\n===Track listing===\n*;CD single (CD1)\n# \"I Love the Way You Love Me\" (Victoria Shaw, Chuck Cannon)\n# \"Waiting for You\" ([[Phil Harding (producer)|Phil Harding]], Ian Curnow, [[Stephen Gately]])\n# \"Let the Message Run Free\" (Ronan Keating, [[Ray Hedges]], Martin Brannigan)\n\n*;CD single (CD2)\n# \"I Love the Way You Love Me\" (Shaw, Cannon) \u2013 3:48\n# \"Grease Medley\" (\"[[Grease (song)|Grease]]\" by [[Barry Gibb]]; \"[[Greased Lightnin' (song)|Greased Lightnin']]\" by [[Jim Jacobs]] and [[Warren Casey]]; \"[[Summer Nights (Grease song)|Summer Nights]]\" by Jim Jacobs and Warren Casey; \"[[You're the One That I Want]]\" by [[John Farrar]]) (Live from Wembley) \u2013 10:13\n# \"[[No Matter What (Boyzone song)|No Matter What]]\" ([[Andrew Lloyd Webber]], [[Jim Steinman]]) (Live from Wembley) \u2013 5:17\n\n===Charts===\n;Weekly charts\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n!Chart (1998-1999)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|28|artist=Boyzone|song=I Love the Way You Love Me}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|36|artist=Boyzone|song=I Love the Way You Love Me}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Europe ([[Eurochart Hot 100]])<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=KwoEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA65-IA7&dq=i+love+the+way+you+love+me+boyzone&hl=en&sa=X&ei=TP6CT8SoHcK_gAeg-b3EBw&ved=0CFkQ6AEwCA#v=onepage&q=i%20love%20the%20way%20you%20love%20me%20boyzone&f=false Eurochart peak]</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|7\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|50|artist=Boyzone|song=I Love the Way You Love Me|songid=3860|accessdate=